    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down, Beckenham, Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Feb: 12.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I have just heard from D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Dodel Port of Zurich that some misfortune has befallen you and that you have been treated shamefully by your Government.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I grieve deeply to hear this, and as soon as you can find a few minutes to spare, I earnestly beg you to let me hear what has happened.</p>
<p>Believe me your friend and admirer | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11877.xml">letter to Arnold Dodel-Port, 12 February 1879</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The letter from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1342.xml">Arnold Dodel-Port</ref> has not been found, but see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11877.xml">letter to Arnold Dodel-Port, 12 February 1879</ref> and n. 3.</note>
        </div>
    
    </body>
